<p>Hey. Recently I&rsquo;ve tried to CURL something like this:</p>
<p><code>curl 'http://localhost?q[param]=value'</code></p>
<p>and I got <code>[globbing] bad range in column</code> error from CURL.
This one is unexpected since I was thinking that using single quotes
do not require any escaping. To find a workaround you can check <code>man curl</code> and
seek for <code>globbing</code>.</p>
<p>So the solution is <code>-g</code> option:</p>
<p><code>curl -g 'http://localhost?q[param]=value'</code></p>
<p>P.S.</p>
<p>Sure you can manually escape square brackets but if your url is pretty long
it can take some time.</p>